id: pmc-emom
title: Fix all-release-tags collapsing legacy historical sections after orphaned git tags
description: "all-release-tags mode uses git tag --list --merged HEAD, which excludes orphaned release tags from rebased/squashed history. Downstream repos like pm-slack-standup have 20 May/June tags that are not merged into main after a history rewrite, causing --all-release-tags to collapse all pre-July items into the oldest reachable release window (2026.7.6) instead of preserving 13+ historical sections.\n\nFix: include ALL matching tags regardless of merge status so orphaned release tags still define release windows. For item-to-release assignment, prefer explicit item.release metadata, then accurate close/update timestamps.\n\nAlso fix audit:prod which fails on inherited allowScripts."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags: []
created_at: "2026-07-13T07:36:13.690Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T08:10:25.044Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-13T08:10:21.275Z"
author: codex-pm-changelog
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T07:45:32.657Z","codex-pm-changelog,created_at=now,text=ROOT CAUSE: listReleaseTags in release-context.ts used 'git tag --list --merged HEAD' which excludes orphaned release tags from rebased/squashed history. pm-slack-standup has 20 May/June tags (v2026.05.26 through v2026.06.14) that are not merged into HEAD after a history rewrite, so --all-release-tags only found 4 July tags and collapsed all 30+ pre-July closed items into the oldest reachable window (2026.7.6).","author=codex-pm-changelog,created_at=now,text=ROOT CAUSE: listReleaseTags in release-context.ts used 'git tag --list --merged HEAD' which excludes orphaned release tags from rebased/squashed history. pm-slack-standup has 20 May/June tags (v2026.05.26 through v2026.06.14) that are not merged into HEAD after a history rewrite, so --all-release-tags only found 4 July tags and collapsed all 30+ pre-July closed items into the oldest reachable window (2026.7.6).\n\nFIX: Removed --merged HEAD from the git tag listing so all matching tags are found regardless of merge status. Chronological sort ensures correct window ordering. Item-to-window assignment prefers explicit item.release metadata (already correct), then time-based assignment using closed_at/updated_at/created_at.\n\nEVIDENCE: pm-slack-standup output now shows 14 historical sections (2026.5.26 through 2026.7.10) instead of 2 collapsed sections. Full test suite: 131 pass, 0 fail. audit:prod environment-neutral (uses env -u npm_config_allow_scripts). Two new regression tests added: resolveReleaseTagWindows includes orphaned tags from non-merged branches + createChangelog preserves historical sections with orphaned-git-tag boundaries.\n\nREVISED: resolveReleaseTagWindows now merges the pending tag into the sorted tags array by timestamp descending (with name tie-breaker) instead of prepending it, so a later-dated orphan tag does not create an inverted window where since > until. Existing test fixture updated: pending v1.3 (May20) follows orphan v9.9.9 (May30) in window order. All 14 pm-slack-standup sections verified with 0 inverted windows."
