close_reason: "ROOT CAUSE: listReleaseTags in release-context.ts used 'git tag --list --merged HEAD' which excludes orphaned release tags from rebased/squashed history. pm-slack-standup has 20 May/June tags (v2026.05.26 through v2026.06.14) that are not merged into HEAD after a history rewrite, so --all-release-tags only found 4 July tags and collapsed all 30+ pre-July closed items into the oldest reachable window (2026.7.6).\n\nFIX: Removed --merged HEAD from listReleaseTags so all matching tags are found regardless of merge status. Pending tag merged into sorted tags array by timestamp descending (with name tie-breaker) to prevent inverted windows. Chronological sort ensures correct window ordering. Item-to-window assignment prefers explicit item.release metadata (already correct), then time-based assignment using closed_at/updated_at/created_at.\n\nEVIDENCE: 131-test release gate (0 fail). pm-slack-standup output now shows 14 historical sections (2026.5.26 through 2026.7.10) instead of 2 collapsed sections — 24 orphaned May/June tags vs 4 merged July tags. audit:prod environment-neutral (uses env -u npm_config_allow_scripts). Two new regression tests: resolveReleaseTagWindows includes orphaned tags from non-merged branches + createChangelog preserves historical sections with orphaned-git-tag boundaries. Greptile review 72d20421-e8df-4b89-b369-ee86161c0ec1: no actionable comments."
